# skill: architect-validate
# purpose: Validate implementation against architectural design
# triggers: Before shipping, during code review

## Invocation
```
architect-validate <task-id> [--design <design-file>] [--impl <impl-directory>]
```

## Output
Creates: `memory/designs/<task-id>/validation.md`

## Validation Checklist
```markdown
# Architectural Validation: <task-id>

## Design Reference
- Design Document: <path>
- ADRs: <list of related ADRs>

## Component Alignment
| Component | Expected | Actual | Status | Notes |
|---|------|---|---|-----|
| <component> | <expected> | <found> | ✓/✗ | <notes> |

## Interface Compliance
| Interface | Contract | Implementation | Status |
|---|---|---|---|
| <API/config> | <spec> | <found> | ✓/✗ |

## Data Flow Verification
- [ ] Data flows as designed
- [ ] No unauthorized data paths
- [ ] Error handling matches design

## Dependency Verification
- [ ] All dependencies declared
- [ ] No unexpected dependencies
- [ ] Version compatibility verified

## Security Alignment
- [ ] Security patterns followed
- [ ] Authentication/authorization as designed
- [ ] Data protection implemented

## Performance Alignment
- [ ] Expected latency acceptable
- [ ] Resource usage within bounds
- [ ] Scalability considerations addressed

## Deviations
| Deviation | Impact | Acceptable | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| <what> | <impact> | Y/N | <why> |

## Overall Assessment
**Status:** ✓ APPROVED | ⚠ APPROVED WITH NOTES | ✗ REQUIRES REVISION

**Recommendations:**
- <recommendation 1>
- <recommendation 2>
```

## Implementation
```bash
#!/bin/bash
# architect-validate.skill implementation

TASK_ID="$1"
DESIGN_FILE="${2:-memory/designs/$TASK_ID/design.md}"
IMPL_DIR="${3:-.}"

if [ ! -f "$DESIGN_FILE" ]; then
    echo "Error: Design file not found: $DESIGN_FILE"
    exit 1
fi

# Parse design and compare to implementation
# This would typically involve:
# 1. Extracting expected components from design
# 2. Scanning implementation for actual components
# 3. Comparing interfaces/APIs
# 4. Validating data flows
# 5. Documenting deviations

VALIDATION_REPORT="memory/designs/$TASK_ID/validation.md"

# Generate validation report (simplified)
cat > "$VALIDATION_REPORT" << EOF
# Architectural Validation: $TASK_ID

## Automated Checks
$(run_component_checks "$DESIGN_FILE" "$IMPL_DIR")

## Manual Review Required
- Interface contracts
- Error handling
- Edge cases

## Overall Status
Pending manual review
EOF

checkpoint --phase custom --description "Architectural validation started for $TASK_ID" \
    --next "Manual review needed before approval"
```
